	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Thursday&#44; 13th Heshvan &#40;October&#41;&#44; 1852</date>.</p>
				<p>My friend and the object of my thoughts&#44; ever before me&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#8220;Whoever oppresses <placeName>Israel</placeName> rises to leadership&#8221;&#42;. I&#44; oppressed<lb/> man&#44; have had to submit to the most despicable cabal. My friends should<lb/> at least have spared me the shameful pains as I have urgently begged<lb/> them to&#44; and such as the relations of a Talmud Haham<add>&#63;</add> justify&#44; and not<lb/> permit the thing to come to such a pass or decision. I urgently re&#45;<lb/>quested of <persName>Wolf</persName> and his partner to make sure of the votes before a meet&#45;<lb/>ing took place. I am very much disgusted and the thing <sic>may&#63;</sic> God forbid&#44;<lb/> spoil another position for me. There is no fear of God in this place.<lb/> Since my return&#44; I suffer very much. I am under spiritual and bodily<lb/> stress. I do not know what to begin. I should like to pronounce my his&#45;<lb/>tory on the basis or subscriptions. What shall I do&#44; &#8220;A millstone is<lb/> around my neck&#8221;&#42;.  In my case &#44; anyone has a chance to &#8220;Obtain entrance to<lb/> Paradise in one hour.&#8221;&#42;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I expect with certainty that in the <date>November</date> issue you will<lb/> continue my discussion. In fact&#44; everything that you have in your posses&#45;<lb/>sion. I am depending upon it&#44; and also that you will correct the mistakes<lb/> which occurred in the <date>October</date> issue. I must urgently ask you to send me<lb/> the proof sheets by return post. I must have them to look them over.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Unfortunately&#44; my <sic>heard</sic> is full&#44; otherwise I would have sent<lb/> you for publication in the <date>December</date> issue&#44; the plan for my history.<lb/> It consists of preface&#44; general introduction&#44; etc.&#44; I am very anxious to<lb/> see all this translated into English by you. With some of it you will<lb/> probably not be in agreement&#44; but the thing must be properly understood.<lb/> I offer a public sanctification of God&#39;s name by breaking the neck of the<lb/> individual critics&#44; such as <persName>Wise</persName>&#44; and other rascals and by setting right<lb/> the better ones&#44; such as <persName>Josh<add>&#63;</add></persName> and <persName>Herzfeld</persName>. I think I shall send you part<lb/> of it tomorrow. What difference does it make if the &#8220;Occident&#8221; appears a<lb/> few days later&#63; It will interest people of this land and others&#44; especi&#45;</p>
				<p>&#42; Talmudic diction<add>&#63;</add></p>
				<p>&#42; Talmudic</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>ally if it is printed in German and English&#44; but at the same time. But&#44;<lb/> in any event&#44; I must have the manuscript back. Please indicate to me<lb/> what you do not understand or cannot read. In case you cannot include<lb/> in the <date>December</date> issue I must have the manuscript back&#44; but you can<lb/> print the German in English characters.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If only I could get well and raise my spirits.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With heartfelt respect&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Sincerely yours&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName></p>
